column8: But his repentance lasted only thirty days ; and , under Cleander 's tyranny , the administration of Perennis was often regretted .

Maximin , abandoned by his guards , was slain in his tent , with his son , ( whom he had associated to the honors of the purple , ) Anulinus the pr??fect , and the principal ministers of his tyranny .
The wealth which the Romans defended against his rapacious tyranny , they freely contributed for his destruction .
To these innocent and illustrious victims of his tyranny , we must add the wife and daughter of the emperor Diocletian .
The sensual connection was refined into a resemblance of the mystic union of Christ with his church , and was pronounced to be indissoluble either by divorce or by death .

His camp , occasionally removed from the banks of the Rhine to those of the Danube , was the seat of his stern despotism , which trampled on every principle of law and justice , and was supported by the avowed power of the sword .
